subject: Re: [junit] Performance issues in executing JUnit Test Cases in AIX
msgSnippet: Hi Clement, ... Without access to an AIX box and your tests, it s quite difficult to guess at the root cause. Could you perhaps describe on a high level what
messageBody:
Hi Clement,

On 10/27/06, clementsingh <clementsingh@...> wrote:
> I am executing JUnit Test Cases using Ant Script in AIX environment.
> In the AIX environment it is taking 71 minutes for the execution at
> the same time same set of scripts are taking 6 minutes in Windows
> environment

Without access to an AIX box and your tests, it's quite difficult to
guess at the root cause. Could you perhaps describe on a high level
what the tests are doing or maybe post a single complete test case
that takes significantly more time to execute on AIX compared to
Windows?

I presume you haven't run the tests inside a profiler on AIX?

Lasse
